#: ../../user_manual/soft_proofing.rst:59
msgid ""
"Enables the black point compensation when converting image to the **proofed output device** profile. Turning this off will clip the shadow values to the minimum that either the screen and the "
"proofing profile can handle, while turning this on will scale the black to the screen-range, showing you the full range of grays in the image. Like :guilabel:`Conversion Rendering Intent`, this "
"value should coincide with the value used by the printing house when performing conversion to the device."
msgstr ""

